the critical skills needed to inspect and maintain wood-burning fireplace inserts to NCSG standards. The course features interactive slides, desktop activities, real-world simulations, and integrates with a Learning Management System. It challenges students with inspections of randomized issues in a virtual residential setting, ensuring they follow all necessary procedures.\n\n**VR Controls and PPE \u2013** Learn how to navigate the virtual environment while getting acquainted with essential personal protective equipment.\n\n**Responsibility & Worksite Hazard Assessment \u2013** Operate in a simulated environment to identify and mitigate hazards commonly encountered during inspections of wood-burning fireplace inserts.\n\n**Familiarization \u2013** Understand different types of wood-burning fireplace inserts and their common features.\n\n**Fireplace Insert Inspection \u2013** Utilize the official NCSG checklist to thoroughly inspect wood-burning fireplace inserts.\n\n**Real-World Simulation \u2013** Complete the inspection by correctly identifying issues with maximum safety awareness and forensic skills.\n\nData reports for review are saved and stored for engagement metrics and simulation performance analysis.\n\nAny off-platform monetization of content accessible in this app conforms to the Oculus Bulk IAP or Subscription Licenses app policy outlined here: https://developer.oculus.com/policy/app-policies", "short_description": "The Hololab National Chimney Sweep Guild Wood Burning Fireplace Inserts VR application equips users with the critical skills necessary to inspect and maintain wood-burning fireplace inserts according to NCSG standards. This in-depth course includes interactive slide content, desktop-based activities, realistic simulations, and comprehensive testing."}]}, "developer_name": null, "developer_privacy_policy_url": "https://ftfvr.com/privacy-app", "developer_terms_of_service_url": null, "publisher_name": "From the Future", "support_website_url": n